Uganda Law Notice

This license is intended to preserve all rights available under Ugandan law and
any other applicable law. Uganda's Copyright and Neighbouring Rights Act,
Chapter 222, including amendments in force from time to time, protects original
works reduced to material form without requiring registration formality. The Act
recognizes computer programmes, electronic data banks, and accompanying
materials as eligible protected works, while ideas, concepts, procedures, and
methods are not protected by copyright on their own.

The repository owner reserves the exclusive economic rights available under
Ugandan copyright law, including the rights to reproduce, publish, distribute,
make available online, communicate to the public, commercially exploit, and
authorize derivative works from the protected materials.

No open-source license is granted. Access to this repository does not transfer
ownership, copyright, patent rights, trade secrets, database rights, trademark
rights, or any other intellectual property rights.

